vivid

--------------------------------------------------

(adjective) Producing powerful feelings or strong, clear images in the mind.

Tạo ra những cảm xúc mạnh mẽ hoặc hình ảnh rõ ràng, sắc nét trong tâm trí.

Examples:
- She has vivid memories of her childhood.
- The dream was so vivid, I could still see it when I woke up.

Synonyms: striking, bright, clear, graphic, intense, powerful, dramatic.

Antonyms: vague, dull, faint, pale, weak, indistinct, unclear.

--------------------------------------------------

(adjective) (of color) Very bright and strong; producing powerful feelings.

(về màu sắc) Rất tươi sáng và mạnh mẽ; tạo ra cảm xúc mạnh mẽ.

Examples:
- The painting was full of vivid colors.
- She wore a vivid red dress to the party.

Synonyms: bright, brilliant, intense, rich, vibrant, strong, deep.

Antonyms: pale, muted, dull, washed-out, subdued, faint, weak.

--------------------------------------------------

(adverb) In a way that produces powerful feelings or strong, clear images in the mind.

Một cách tạo ra những cảm xúc mạnh mẽ hoặc hình ảnh rõ ràng, sắc nét trong tâm trí.

Examples:
- He vividly described the scene of the accident.
- I can still vividly remember the day we first met.

Synonyms: graphically, clearly, intensely, powerfully, dramatically, realistically.

Antonyms: vaguely, faintly, dimly, indistinctly, unclearly, weakly, subtly.

--------------------------------------------------